The Story of Uhrlik<br>
Epilogue<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp So Uhrlik dispensed justice on the dark elf Ambassador Dvinn. Thus quieting the memories of his parents and allowing countless spirits to rest in peace. The accursed Hatred that infected Uhrlik’s blood did not dissipate with the slaying of Dvinn. He suspected that it would not until he stormed the gates of Hate and destroyed Innoruuk himself.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He spoke at length with Brenidil about these friends. They turned out to be a guild, a collection of noble spirits like him that would welcome him with open arms. It was the guild that he would soon join, The Feir’Dal, The Good Elves. In Feir’Dal he found a home at long last. He found friends. Eventually, he would find a wife and lose a brother.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp There were many stories in Uhrlik’s life that took place before, during and after his search for vengeance. There were friends along the way that were not present within these meager pages. There were stories that shaped his life and the face of Norrath forever. Those, however, are stories for another time…<br>
